## Generations of Microprocessors

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. First-generation

• From 1971 to 1972
• Processors included:

* INTEL 4004
* Rockwell international PPS-4
* INTEL 8008

### 2. Second generation

• From 1973 to 1978
• Development of 8-bit microprocessors
• Processors included:

* INTEL 8085
* Motorola 6800
* Motorola 6801

### 3. Third generation

• From 1979 to 1980
• Introduced 16-bit processors
• Processors included:

* INTEL 8086
* 80186
* 80286
* Motorola 68000
* Motorola 68010
  • Used HMOS technology

### 4. Fourth generation

• From 1981 to 1995
• 32-bit processors introduced
• Used HMOS fabrication
• Popular processors:

* INTEL 80386
* Motorola 68020

### 5. Fifth-generation

• From 1995 till now
• 64-bit processors introduced
• Included:

* PENTIUM
* Celeron
* Dual-core processors
* Quad-core processors
* Octa-core processors

