## Types of Microprocessors

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Complex Instruction Set           │
│       Microprocessor (CISC)             │
│ DEFINITION: Processors designed to      │
│ minimize the number of instructions     │
│ per program and ignore the number of   │
│ cycles per instruction.                 │
│ CONTEXT: Uses compiler translation      │
│ from high-level language to assembly.   │
│ EXAMPLE: IBM 370/168, VAX 11/780        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

Features:
• Shorter code length
• Extra RAM used to store instructions
• Performs downloading, uploading and recalling data from memory
• Performs complex mathematical calculations in a single command

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Reduced Instruction Set           │
│       Microprocessor (RISC)             │
│ DEFINITION: Processors designed to      │
│ reduce execution time using simplified  │
│ instruction sets.                       │
│ CONTEXT: Requires one clock cycle for   │
│ execution in many cases.                │
│ EXAMPLE: Power PC 601, 604, 615, 620    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

Features:
• Faster execution
• Uses LOAD and STORE instructions
• Less number of transistors
• More registers

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Superscalar Microprocessor        │
│ DEFINITION: Processors capable of       │
│ performing many tasks simultaneously.   │
│ CONTEXT: Uses multiple operation units. │
│ EXAMPLE: ALU and multiplier arrays      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Application-Specific Integrated   │
│       Circuit (ASIC)                    │
│ DEFINITION: Processors designed for     │
│ application-specific tasks.             │
│ CONTEXT: Used in personal digital       │
│ assistant computers.                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Digital Signal Multiprocessor     │
│ DEFINITION: Processors used to convert  │
│ analog to digital or digital to analog  │
│ signals.                                │
│ CONTEXT: Used in RADAR, SONAR, home     │
│ theatres.                               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

