## Features of Modern Microprocessors

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Clock speed
   • Refers to the speed at which processor executes instructions
   • Modern processors operate in GHz

2. Instruction set architecture
   • Includes CISC and RISC architectures
   • Affects efficiency and complexity

3. Cache memory
   • High-speed memory storing frequently used data

4. Multi-core processors
   • Multiple cores execute tasks simultaneously

5. Virtualization
   • Enables multiple operating systems on same hardware

6. Power management
   • Reduces power consumption
   • Improves energy efficiency

7. Graphics processing
   • Integrated GPUs handle graphics-intensive tasks

8. Security features
   • Hardware-level encryption
   • Secure boot mechanisms

9. Internet connectivity
   • Includes Wi-Fi and Ethernet capabilities

10. Machine learning capabilities
    • Specialized units for AI and machine learning tasks

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Advantages of Microprocessors

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. High processing speed
2. Compact size
3. Easy maintenance
4. Can perform complex mathematics
5. Flexible
6. Can be improved according to requirement

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Disadvantages of Microprocessors

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. Overheating occurs due to overuse
2. Performance depends on the size of the data
3. Large board size than microcontrollers
4. Most microprocessors do not support floating-point operations

