📝 DETAILED EXPLANATION:

**Components:**

1. Input Unit
   • Position: Left side
   • Function: Accepts data from user
   • Examples: Mouse, Keyboard

2. CPU
   • Position: Center
   • Function: Performs processing operations
   • Contains ALU and Control Unit

3. ALU
   • Position: Inside CPU
   • Function: Performs arithmetic and logical operations

4. Control Unit
   • Position: Inside CPU
   • Function: Controls all CPU activities

5. Memory Unit
   • Position: Top
   • Function: Stores data and instructions

6. Output Unit
   • Position: Right side
   • Function: Displays processed results

**Relationships & Flow:**
• Input unit sends data to CPU
• CPU processes data using ALU and Control Unit
• Memory stores instructions and intermediate results
• Output unit displays final results

