## Functional Units Explanation

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Input Unit

• Used to read data into computer
• Common devices:

* Keyboard
* Mouse
* Joystick
* Trackball
* Microphone

### Central Processing Unit

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Central Processing Unit (CPU)     │
│ DEFINITION: Electronic circuitry that   │
│ executes instructions given by a        │
│ computer program.                       │
│ CONTEXT: Performs arithmetic, logical,  │
│ control and I/O operations.             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

### Memory Unit

• Storage area where running programs are kept
• Contains data needed by programs
• Categories:

* Primary memory
* Secondary memory
  • Enables processor to access running applications

### Arithmetic & Logical Unit

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Arithmetic & Logical Unit (ALU)   │
│ DEFINITION: Unit that performs          │
│ arithmetic and logical operations.      │
│ CONTEXT: Executes addition, subtraction,│
│ multiplication, division, AND, OR, NOT. │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

### Control Unit

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Control Unit                      │
│ DEFINITION: Coordinates operations of   │
│ processor and controls system activity. │
│ CONTEXT: Directs memory, ALU and I/O    │
│ devices.                                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

⚠️ IMPORTANT NOTE:
The control unit is known as the nerve center of the computer system.

### Output Unit

• Sends processed results to user
• Output devices display information understandable to user
• Common example: Monitor

