## Common / Shared Bus v/s Dedicated Bus

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Dedicated Bus

• Assigned to a single function
• Example: Address bus
• Can connect physical subset of components
• Example: I/O bus connects all I/O modules

### Common Bus

• Can be used for addresses and data
• Requires address valid control line
• Uses time multiplexing

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Time Multiplexing                 │
│ DEFINITION: Using same lines for        │
│ multiple purposes.                      │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

