## Serial V/S Parallel Bus

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Parallel Bus

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Parallel Bus                      │
│ DEFINITION: Communication method that   │
│ transmits multiple bits simultaneously  │
│ using multiple wires.                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

Advantages of Parallel Bus:

1. Faster data transfer
2. Simplicity of implementation

🔬 PRACTICAL APPLICATION:
Used in video processing and image rendering applications.

### Serial Bus

📘 DEFINITION:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ TERM: Serial Bus                        │
│ DEFINITION: Communication method that   │
│ transmits data sequentially one bit at  │
│ a time over single wire/channel.        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘

Advantages of Serial Bus:

1. Simplified wiring
2. Longer distance transmission

🔬 PRACTICAL APPLICATION:
Used in networking and telecommunications.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Serial vs Parallel Comparison

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

• Parallel link transmits several streams simultaneously
• Serial link transmits single stream

• Serial links can be clocked faster than parallel links

• Serial is cheaper to implement

• Serial requires fewer cables and occupies less space

• Many ICs use serial interfaces because fewer pins are needed

• Parallel buses widely used within integrated circuits

• Parallel buses common in earlier systems

• Serial buses prevalent in modern computers

• Parallel transmission transfers multiple bits simultaneously

• Parallel transmission requires more channels

• Parallel is easier to program

• SCSI buses are parallel buses

• Serial buses used for long-distance communication
Example: Computer to computer

• Parallel buses used for short distance
Example: Computer to printer

• Serial transmission is full duplex

• Parallel transmission is half duplex

• Serial transmission cables are thinner, longer and economical

